Here's a Java solution that checks if the input number is a power of three without using loops or recursion. It does this by comparing the logarithm base 3 of the input number to an integer value, using the `Math.log10()` function to perform the logarithm calculation.
```
public class PowerOfThree {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }
        return (Math.log10(n) / Math.log10(3) - (int) (Math.log10(n) / Math.log10(3))) == 0;
    }
}
```
